com.pstmetro.generics

Class ArrayMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pstmetro.generics.ArrayMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of Keys stored within the ArrayMapEntry.
    V - The type of Values stored within the ArrayMapEntry
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>

    public class ArrayMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Map<K,V>
    The ArrayMap class is merely a custom implementation of a Map that is backed by an Array of ArrayMapEntry objects. We created this class to prove that we are able to create efficient Data structures.
